{
  "texts": [
    "This approach involved conducting confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) to examine the measurement model, followed by structural equation modeling (SEM), as detailed in the next section.",
    "Prior to analysis, we thoroughly cleaned the data and addressed various issues.",
    "Out of the 588 collected questionnaires, 551 were included in the study for subsequent analysis after excluding invalid or incomplete questionnaires, with an effective proportion of 93.7%.",
    "The data collected in this study showed that female respondents accounted for 65.34%, possibly due to the higher frequency of apparel consumption among female consumers (Sadiq et al., 2021).",
    "Approximately 51.18% of the respondents were born between 1995 and 1999, followed by respondents born between 2000 and 2004, accounting for 48.82%."
  ]
}